<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="168" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (<persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>)/6–2345: Telegram</note>
                        <head>No. 168 <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="from">Truman</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2" type="to">Marshal Stalin</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d168fn1">Presumably sent to the United States
                                Naval Attaché, Moscow, via the White House Map Room and Navy
                                channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="2" xml:id="d168fn2">For the
                                    full text of this message, see <ref target="#d570">document No.
                                        570</ref>.</note></seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Olympia,
                                        Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-25">25 June 1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>304 …</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>Should there be any further aspect of the agreement<note n="3" xml:id="d168fn3">i. e., the Anglo-American-Yugoslav agreement
                                relating to Venezia Giulia, signed at Belgrade, June 9, 1945
                                (Executive Agreement Series No. 501; 59 <gloss target="#t_Stat1">Stat</gloss>. (2) 1855).</note> which you feel should be
                            considered, we shall have an opportunity to discuss this at our early
                            meeting.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>